FILE: routes.rs
MOD: api/routes
ROLE: HTTP route handlers — project/agent registration, message send, presence, channel subscribe, message retrieval, tool registry
EP: router; register_project; register_agent; send_message; update_presence; get_messages; peek_messages; subscribe_channel; unsubscribe_channel; list_agents; update_agent_description; register_tool_entry; list_tools; get_tool_entry; delete_tool_entry; health
STAB: volatile
INV:
  - All auth-gated routes use AgentAuth extractor — agent identity comes from X-Agent-Name header, not request body
  - PATCH /agents/{name} (update_agent_description) enforces self-update only: path name must match auth agent name, else 403; max 500 chars
  - GET /agents accepts ?include_offline=true to merge DB-registered offline agents into response
  - register_agent accepts optional description field; blank re-registration preserves existing description (COALESCE)
  - send_message validates stanza from= matches authenticated agent (T8b) before dispatching
  - register_agent enforces no-dot constraint on agent names before calling broker
  - POST /agents/register is body-auth only (first-contact route — no X-Agent-Name header yet)
  - AmbiguousMention dispatch error maps to 400 with disambiguation message listing conflicting projects
  - CrossProjectNotFound maps to 404; CrossProjectDenied maps to 403
  - PresenceRequest no longer has a name field — name comes from AgentAuth extractor
  - PUT /tools/{name} requires AgentAuth; GET /tools and GET /tools/{name} are open (no auth)
  - DELETE /tools/{name} requires AgentAuth; any authenticated agent can deregister (no ownership enforcement)
  - Tool name validation: reject leading/trailing whitespace → 400; empty → 400; > 128 chars → 400
  - Tool description must be non-empty and non-whitespace → 400 if blank; > 2000 chars → 400
  - Tool routes are in exempt_routes (no rate limiting) — consistent with agent registration
LOOK: AgentAuth extractor; send_message T8b check; AmbiguousMention error arm; register_agent dot guard; update_agent_description self-check; register_tool_entry validation block
CHK: cargo test; arch fitness (api in allowed list for broker-callers, db-callers, stanza-callers)
CNTR: api/routes::send_message depends_on broker/state::dispatch_stanza
DEPS-ON: broker/state; broker/delivery; stanza/types
